# Awareness Pipeline — Remaining Work

## FIXED: cluster_id enforcement permanently breaking inter-service calls
Root cause: two bugs working together:
1. security.defaultValidator cached cluster_id forever with no TTL — if first
   read got wrong value or failed, it was stuck for the process lifetime.
2. InternalDialOption() (used by AI services) silently fell back to insecure
   when certs weren't ready, but never attached cluster_id to metadata.
   The globular_client framework already did this, but the raw dial path didn't.
Fix (3 changes):
- security/cluster.go: defaultValidator now has 2-min TTL + mutex (self-heals)
- globular_service/services.go: new InternalDialOptions() adds cluster_id
  metadata interceptor alongside TLS creds (belt-and-suspenders)
- globular-quickstart seed-etcd.sh: added cluster_id + bootstrapped to system config

## After cluster_id is fixed, verify the full chain:
1. Kill a node in Docker simulation
2. Controller detects unhealthy (2 min) — already works
3. Controller emits "cluster.health.degraded" event — currently blocked by auth
4. Event service stores in ScyllaDB — ScyllaDB consistency fix done
5. AI Watcher receives event via subscription — code ready, untested
6. Cluster Doctor uses health data — code ready, untested

## Issues found during failure testing (observe, don't patch yet):

### Node agent resolves new leader on port 443 instead of 12000
After leader failover, agents refresh endpoint to mesh port (443) instead of
direct gRPC port (12000). This routes through Envoy which may strip auth metadata.
Seen in scenario #3 (leader kill).

### Reconciler says "cluster clean" with dead nodes
The reconcile workflow doesn't factor node liveness into drift assessment.
A dead node is not "clean." Seen in scenario #1.

### Event service not found on compute nodes
Node agents call ResolveLocalServiceAddr("event.EventService") which filters by
local IP. Event service runs on control-plane nodes only. Compute nodes can never
find it. Fix: use ResolveServiceAddr() (cluster-wide) instead.

### etcd client retry has no backoff
During quorum loss, etcd clients spam DeadlineExceeded every 1-3 seconds with
no exponential backoff. Noisy logs. Seen in scenario #7.

